---
import QuestionLayout from '@layouts/QuestionLayout.astro';

const relatedLinks = [];
const _body = "<p>A placement target declares which runtime environment a capability can execute in. It is part of the capability contract. The runtime uses it to decide whether a capability can be selected for a given request.</p>\n\n      <p>When a request arrives, it includes a <span class=\"code-inline\">requested_target</span>. The runtime only considers capabilities whose contract lists that target in <span class=\"code-inline\">preferred_targets</span>. A capability that does not list a target cannot be placed there.</p>\n\n      <h2>Supported targets</h2>\n      <div class=\"target-grid\">\n        <div class=\"target-card\">\n          <div class=\"target-card-name\">local <span class=\"badge-status badge-done\">v0.7.0</span></div>\n          <div class=\"target-card-desc\">Development and testing. Runs in-process on the local machine. Fully implemented.</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"target-card\">\n          <div class=\"target-card-name\">browser <span class=\"badge-status badge-planned\">planned</span></div>\n          <div class=\"target-card-desc\">Browser via WASM adapter. The browser adapter crate exists and is partially built.</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"target-card\">\n          <div class=\"target-card-name\">edge <span class=\"badge-status badge-planned\">planned</span></div>\n          <div class=\"target-card-desc\">CDN edge workers (Cloudflare Workers, Deno Deploy). Specified, not yet released.</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"target-card\">\n          <div class=\"target-card-name\">cloud <span class=\"badge-status badge-planned\">planned</span></div>\n          <div class=\"target-card-desc\">Server-side cloud execution. Specified, not yet released.</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"target-card\">\n          <div class=\"target-card-name\">ai-pipeline <span class=\"badge-status badge-planned\">planned</span></div>\n          <div class=\"target-card-desc\">AI agent runtimes. MCP integration is live but full ai-pipeline placement is planned.</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <h2>How the contract declares targets</h2>\n      <div class=\"code-block\">[[capabilities]]\nname = \"plan-expedition\"\nversion = \"0.2.0\"\npreferred_targets = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n\n[capabilities.constraints]\nnetwork_access = false\nfilesystem_access = false</div>\n\n      <p>This capability can be placed on <span class=\"code-inline\">local</span> or <span class=\"code-inline\">cloud</span>. A request with <span class=\"code-inline\">requested_target = \"browser\"</span> would not select it.</p>\n\n      <h2>What happens at runtime</h2>\n      <p>During the <span class=\"code-inline\">discovering</span> state, the runtime filters capabilities by goal and placement target. During <span class=\"code-inline\">evaluating_constraints</span>, it checks whether the sandbox constraints are compatible with the target environment. Both checks must pass before a capability reaches the <span class=\"code-inline\">selecting</span> state.</p>\n\n      <h2>Why placement targets matter</h2>\n      <p>The same WASM binary can, in principle, run anywhere WASM runs. But not every capability should. A capability that writes to local disk should not be placed on an edge node. Placement targets let the contract author be explicit about this. The runtime enforces it.</p>";
const _jsonLd = "{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How do placement targets work in Traverse?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"A placement target tells the runtime which environment a capability can run in. Supported targets: browser, edge, cloud, ai-pipeline, local. The contract lists preferred_targets and the runtime only selects capabilities that support the requested target.\"}}]}";
---
<QuestionLayout
  title={"How do placement targets work in Traverse?"}
  description={"Placement targets tell the Traverse runtime which environments a capability can run in. Supported targets: browser, edge, cloud, ai-pipeline, local. Only local is fully implemented in v0.7.0."}
  canonical={"https://traverse-framework.com/questions/how-do-placement-targets-work.html"}
  category={"Technical Architecture"}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  jsonLd={_jsonLd}
>
  <Fragment set:html={_body} />
</QuestionLayout>
